00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:09,760
Alright,

3
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:15,980
so we were in the midst of talking about symmetry.

4
00:00:18,260 --> 00:00:21,420
Symmetries are operations that you can do

5
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:24,580
on a system which don't change the description,

6
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,440
which don't change the phenomena,

7
00:00:28,440 --> 00:00:31,560
which don't change the energy levels,

8
00:00:31,780 --> 00:00:36,120
which don't change the values of the energies of systems.

9
00:00:36,580 --> 00:00:38,340
That's not ours,

10
00:00:38,340 --> 00:00:38,880
I don't think.

11
00:00:41,360 --> 00:00:42,460
In particular,

12
00:00:42,460 --> 00:00:43,800
they don't change the values

13
00:00:43,800 --> 00:00:45,140
of the energies of a system.

14
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:48,840
Examples that we talked about were translation.

15
00:00:49,560 --> 00:00:53,060
If you take an atom with a given energy,

16
00:00:53,060 --> 00:00:55,620
and you move it from one place to another,

17
00:00:55,620 --> 00:00:56,760
the energy doesn't change.

18
00:00:58,080 --> 00:01:00,640
Doesn't matter which atomic state you study,

19
00:01:00,860 --> 00:01:02,640
it's not just true for the ground state,

20
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:04,720
it's true for every atomic state.

21
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:10,060
And so,

22
00:01:10,060 --> 00:01:16,760
the Hamiltonian doesn't change when you move things.

23
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,100
That's a symmetry.

24
00:01:18,460 --> 00:01:20,280
The Schrodinger equation doesn't change.

25
00:01:20,500 --> 00:01:21,800
Same Schrodinger equation.

26
00:01:23,060 --> 00:01:26,020
Same thing is true for rotating a system.

27
00:01:26,520 --> 00:01:29,200
We're going to talk a lot tonight about rotating systems.

28
00:01:34,580 --> 00:01:38,460
Another example is just interchanging two particles,

29
00:01:38,460 --> 00:01:39,720
two identical particles.

30
00:01:40,460 --> 00:01:42,360
You might call one electron,

31
00:01:42,360 --> 00:01:43,260
electron one,

32
00:01:43,260 --> 00:01:44,460
and the other electron,

33
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:45,340
electron two.

34
00:01:45,760 --> 00:01:47,400
You might call them Harry and Fred.

35
00:01:49,520 --> 00:01:51,460
Changing the names of the electrons,

36
00:01:51,460 --> 00:01:53,960
interchanging electron one with electron two,

37
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:59,080
doesn't change the properties of an atom.

38
00:02:00,020 --> 00:02:01,400
So that's also a symmetry.

39
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,430
We tend not to think of it as

40
00:02:04,430 --> 00:02:06,220
a symmetry just because we're so used to it.

41
00:02:06,280 --> 00:02:07,720
Identical particles are identical,

42
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,620
so it doesn't matter what you name them.

43
00:02:10,020 --> 00:02:11,160
But it is a symmetry.

44
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:14,760
And there are other symmetries of physics.

45
00:02:16,140 --> 00:02:17,060
For example,

46
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:18,100
if you have a crystal lattice,

47
00:02:18,100 --> 00:02:22,020
a crystal lattice has a kind of translation symmetry.

48
00:02:23,620 --> 00:02:27,300
It's not translation symmetry in space.

49
00:02:27,720 --> 00:02:29,960
It is translation symmetry in space,

50
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:33,180
but a different kind of translation symmetry in space.

51
00:02:33,840 --> 00:02:38,440
It's just translating everything by one lattice unit.

52
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,680
If we had a very,

53
00:02:40,680 --> 00:02:41,420
very long,

54
00:02:41,420 --> 00:02:45,060
almost infinite crystal,

55
00:02:45,580 --> 00:02:48,080
then it's almost a perfect symmetry.

56
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:52,280
To translate from one atom to the,

57
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:52,580
you know,

58
00:02:52,620 --> 00:02:55,960
to translate the whole system by one lattice spacing.

59
00:02:56,480 --> 00:02:57,200
Of course,

60
00:02:57,200 --> 00:02:58,840
there it's not exactly a symmetry

61
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,480
if the system is not infinite.

62
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:02,820
If the system is not infinite,

63
00:03:02,820 --> 00:03:04,560
then there are boundaries to the crystal.

64
00:03:04,760 --> 00:03:05,240
Well,

65
00:03:05,240 --> 00:03:06,860
then you can't really translate it.

66
00:03:06,940 --> 00:03:08,000
But if the crystal went

67
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,060
on and on and on forever,

68
00:03:10,260 --> 00:03:11,680
then you could do two things.

69
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:16,340
You could imagine taking the crystal,

70
00:03:20,359 --> 00:03:23,160
and moving the entire crystal a little bit.

71
00:03:28,080 --> 00:03:29,120
This one goes to here,

72
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:29,940
this one goes to here,

73
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:30,720
this one goes to here,

74
00:03:30,720 --> 00:03:31,520
this one goes to here.

75
00:03:33,260 --> 00:03:34,860
That is a symmetry of a crystal.

76
00:03:35,140 --> 00:03:35,780
That's true.

77
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,340
It's a symmetry of anything.

78
00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:40,340
The ability to move it from one place to another.

79
00:03:40,800 --> 00:03:43,220
But the crystal has a different symmetry,

80
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,940
which is just,

81
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:47,860
just,

82
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,900
translating from,

83
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,020
let's call this one,

84
00:03:52,020 --> 00:03:52,980
two,

85
00:03:52,980 --> 00:03:53,740
three,

86
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:54,560
four,

87
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,920
and let's suppose it goes on

88
00:03:55,920 --> 00:03:57,160
and on and on forever and ever.

89
00:03:58,420 --> 00:04:00,870
Just relabeling the crystal so that

90
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:03,320
this one is now called minus one,

91
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,080
this one is called,

92
00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:05,120
no,

93
00:04:05,120 --> 00:04:05,360
no,

94
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:05,680
not one,

95
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:06,160
minus one,

96
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:06,460
zero,

97
00:04:06,460 --> 00:04:07,060
one,

98
00:04:07,060 --> 00:04:07,620
two,

99
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,160
three.

100
00:04:08,640 --> 00:04:10,340
Imagine the crystal goes on and on.

101
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,220
That's also a symmetry.

102
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:15,300
Translation of crystals by the crystal,

103
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:17,440
by the crystal lattice spacing.

104
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:19,560
What else?

105
00:04:19,720 --> 00:04:21,360
What other symmetries are there?

106
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,340
There are lots.

107
00:04:23,460 --> 00:04:24,400
There are lots,

108
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,000
but,

109
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:29,660
some of them are more abstract than others.

110
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,840
The physically intuitive ones

111
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:38,260
tend to have to do with properties of space.

112
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,240
The homogeneity of space,

113
00:04:41,540 --> 00:04:43,740
the fact that every point is like every other point,

114
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:45,760
is translation symmetry.

115
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:47,880
The isotropy of space,

116
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:50,740
the fact that every direction is like every other direction,

117
00:04:50,940 --> 00:04:52,480
is rotational symmetry.

118
00:04:54,800 --> 00:04:55,460
Now,

119
00:04:58,199 --> 00:04:59,520
another concept

120
00:05:00,580 --> 00:05:01,420
that is,

121
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:03,340
we'll see is related to symmetry,

122
00:05:03,660 --> 00:05:04,880
not the same thing,

123
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,560
is called degeneracy.

124
00:05:08,260 --> 00:05:10,200
Degeneracy and then specifically

125
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:12,140
degeneracy of energy levels.

126
00:05:13,260 --> 00:05:16,140
Degeneracy of energy levels is simply the statement

127
00:05:16,140 --> 00:05:18,400
an energy level of a system

128
00:05:18,880 --> 00:05:20,640
is said to be degenerate

129
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:22,390
if there's more than one

130
00:05:22,390 --> 00:05:24,140
state with the same energy level.

131
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,120
Then that energy level is called degenerate.

132
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:31,240
When does it happen,

133
00:05:32,080 --> 00:05:36,800
for a random system with a generic Hamiltonian,

134
00:05:36,920 --> 00:05:40,500
assuming that the spectrum of it is,

135
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,000
discrete spectrum,

136
00:05:43,160 --> 00:05:46,920
some sort of discrete spectrum of energy levels,

137
00:05:47,180 --> 00:05:48,820
it would be an accident,

138
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:50,680
it would be a rather odd accident,

139
00:05:51,240 --> 00:05:54,260
that two levels would have exactly the same energy.

140
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,580
And when I say exactly,

141
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,300
I mean exactly the same energy.

142
00:05:57,580 --> 00:05:59,095
They may have the same energy to

143
00:05:59,095 --> 00:06:00,610
one part in 10 to the 15th,

144
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:03,940
but to say they have exactly the same energy,

145
00:06:04,060 --> 00:06:06,240
what kind of coincidence would that take?

146
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:07,780
Well,

147
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:09,900
as we'll see,

148
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:12,400
it doesn't necessarily take a coincidence,

149
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,280
it takes a symmetry.

150
00:06:16,500 --> 00:06:17,580
In fact,

151
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:19,000
those are the only cases

152
00:06:19,900 --> 00:06:23,840
where we really believe that there are true degeneracies,

153
00:06:23,860 --> 00:06:25,460
exact degeneracies of nature,

154
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,720
when there are symmetries.

155
00:06:32,540 --> 00:06:33,920
Degeneracies sometimes,

156
00:06:34,859 --> 00:06:35,580
no,

157
00:06:37,299 --> 00:06:38,020
sometimes,

158
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,220
not degeneracy,

159
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:39,840
sometimes,

160
00:06:39,900 --> 00:06:40,680
means symmetry,

161
00:06:40,900 --> 00:06:41,480
the other way.

162
00:06:42,080 --> 00:06:45,120
Symmetries sometimes imply degeneracy,

163
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:46,160
but not always.

164
00:06:46,620 --> 00:06:48,060
And I'm gonna show you now,

165
00:06:48,120 --> 00:06:49,460
I'm gonna begin with an example

166
00:06:49,460 --> 00:06:53,900
in which you can see sort of intuitively

167
00:06:54,900 --> 00:07:00,880
how symmetries and when symmetries imply degeneracy.

168
00:07:04,079 --> 00:07:07,720
That incidentally is one of the main uses of symmetry

169
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,880
to analyze the energy,

170
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:11,440
the energy spectrums of systems,

171
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:15,860
and see that they have levels that exactly match.

172
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:17,580
That can be very important.

173
00:07:17,900 --> 00:07:18,600
In atoms,

174
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,760
it's extremely important.

175
00:07:22,440 --> 00:07:24,700
Let's start with rotation symmetry.

176
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:28,040
Let's start with rotation symmetry.

177
00:07:28,360 --> 00:07:31,040
And I wanna think about a very simple system,

178
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:34,460
namely a particle moving on a circle.

179
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:38,400
It could be a particle moving on a circular wire.

