00:12:07,660 --> 00:12:08,560
for it to be Hermitian.

292
00:12:08,740 --> 00:12:09,540
After all,

293
00:12:09,600 --> 00:12:12,380
Hermitian is the analog among operators

294
00:12:12,380 --> 00:12:13,880
as being real,

295
00:12:14,439 --> 00:12:16,300
but I guarantee you

296
00:12:16,300 --> 00:12:17,380
that i has to be there.

297
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,940
Go back in your notes

298
00:12:18,940 --> 00:12:20,380
to the study of momentum,

299
00:12:21,420 --> 00:12:22,820
and you'll find out

300
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:24,100
why that i has to be there.

301
00:12:24,680 --> 00:12:26,700
And that's called the angular momentum.

302
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:30,640
That's usually denoted L.

303
00:12:31,060 --> 00:12:31,540
And that's the angular momentum

304
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:33,360
of the angular momentum.

305
00:12:33,360 --> 00:12:33,700
Y L?

306
00:12:33,900 --> 00:12:35,100
Don't know Y L.

307
00:12:36,740 --> 00:12:38,120
Y P for momentum?

308
00:12:38,460 --> 00:12:39,940
Don't know Y P for momentum.

309
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:44,580
But L is the angular momentum.

310
00:12:45,300 --> 00:12:46,220
And so,

311
00:12:46,220 --> 00:12:47,160
we can write

312
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,140
that the change in psi

313
00:12:50,260 --> 00:12:54,180
under the operation of infinitesimal rotation

314
00:12:55,310 --> 00:12:56,400
is governed by

315
00:12:57,640 --> 00:12:58,660
minus i

316
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:00,600
times the action

317
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,760
of the angular momentum operator

318
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:04,360
on psi.

319
00:13:06,410 --> 00:13:07,760
That identifies,

320
00:13:07,840 --> 00:13:09,400
according to the definitions

321
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:10,600
of last week,

322
00:13:11,349 --> 00:13:13,060
that identifies L

323
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,600
as the generator of rotations.

324
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:19,540
If you can't remember

325
00:13:19,540 --> 00:13:20,920
the precise definition,

326
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:22,820
let's just say

327
00:13:22,820 --> 00:13:24,520
that this is the definition

328
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:27,420
of the generator

329
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:29,420
of a symmetry operation.

330
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:30,580
It's the generator

331
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:32,420
If the symmetry operation is such

332
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:35,700
that it has a version of it

333
00:13:35,700 --> 00:13:37,960
for arbitrarily small parameter,

334
00:13:38,460 --> 00:13:39,780
in this case angle,

335
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,800
then the definition of the generator

336
00:13:43,439 --> 00:13:46,500
is just in terms of the small change

337
00:13:46,500 --> 00:13:47,420
in the wave function

338
00:13:48,540 --> 00:13:52,200
when you shift by an infinitesimal amount,

339
00:13:53,060 --> 00:13:55,780
and that will just give you the generator.

340
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:56,760
You lost an epsilon.

341
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:57,600
Don't worry.

342
00:13:57,600 --> 00:13:58,720
I did lose an epsilon.

343
00:14:02,860 --> 00:14:03,480
I did lose an epsilon.

344
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:04,660
I did lose an epsilon,

345
00:14:04,900 --> 00:14:06,060
and this defines L,

346
00:14:06,220 --> 00:14:08,340
and L is minus i d by d theta.

347
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:10,960
Okay.

348
00:14:11,920 --> 00:14:13,860
And L is known as the angular momentum.

349
00:14:14,660 --> 00:14:15,140
Now,

350
00:14:15,140 --> 00:14:16,100
before I go on,

351
00:14:16,120 --> 00:14:17,980
I want to put in some H bars.

352
00:14:19,920 --> 00:14:21,800
I'll surely drop them again,

353
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:23,660
but just to remind you where they go.

354
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:26,400
The precise definition,

355
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:28,100
including H bars,

356
00:14:28,180 --> 00:14:29,880
when we don't set H bar to one,

357
00:14:30,520 --> 00:14:32,400
contains an H bar over here.

358
00:14:34,540 --> 00:14:36,540
That's the same H bar that occurs

359
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:37,460
in the momentum,

360
00:14:37,760 --> 00:14:42,080
P equals minus i H bar d by dx.

361
00:14:43,820 --> 00:14:44,980
Same H bar,

362
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,980
and it's a little bit arbitrary

363
00:14:50,980 --> 00:14:52,180
where we put it,

364
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:55,140
but putting it over here,

365
00:14:55,140 --> 00:14:57,160
I guess we would say that

366
00:14:57,860 --> 00:15:00,880
the change in psi is i

367
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:03,900
epsilon over H bar times L.

368
00:15:04,140 --> 00:15:04,700
Now,

369
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:05,940
probably here and there,

370
00:15:06,580 --> 00:15:09,940
just to remind you and to keep you awake,

371
00:15:10,220 --> 00:15:11,580
I will put in H bars

372
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:13,940
now and then,

373
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:15,540
every so often,

374
00:15:16,320 --> 00:15:16,880
randomly.

375
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:20,720
Okay.

376
00:15:28,300 --> 00:15:30,060
What are the eigenvectors

377
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:32,180
of the angular momentum?

378
00:15:33,040 --> 00:15:34,900
The eigenvectors of the ang-

379
00:15:34,900 --> 00:15:36,100
and the eigenvalues.

380
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:38,660
The eigenvalues are the values

381
00:15:38,660 --> 00:15:40,820
of the possible outcomes of experiments,

382
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,940
and the eigenvectors are the states

383
00:15:43,940 --> 00:15:45,160
of the system which-

384
00:15:45,160 --> 00:15:47,420
for which those outcomes are certain.

385
00:15:48,040 --> 00:15:48,860
All right,

386
00:15:48,860 --> 00:15:49,560
to answer that,

387
00:15:49,780 --> 00:15:53,160
we write the equation L on psi,

388
00:15:55,140 --> 00:15:57,240
that's the action of the angular momentum,

389
00:15:58,040 --> 00:16:00,780
is equal to an eigenvalue,

390
00:16:01,060 --> 00:16:03,200
I'm going to call that eigenvalue M.

391
00:16:05,220 --> 00:16:06,260
It's standard.

392
00:16:06,760 --> 00:16:08,340
M times psi.

393
00:16:11,880 --> 00:16:12,480
Now,

394
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,900
if I were doing it,

395
00:16:13,960 --> 00:16:15,420
I would have put little L here,

396
00:16:15,680 --> 00:16:18,380
but somebody did this long in the past.

397
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:21,880
M happens to stand for magnetic quantum number,

398
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:24,800
but that's a historical,

399
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:25,120
and it's not a real number,

400
00:16:25,120 --> 00:16:25,740
it's a real anachronism.

401
00:16:25,980 --> 00:16:26,560
Nevertheless,

402
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,940
the eigenvalue of L,

403
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:31,200
and let's add a little more to this picture.

404
00:16:31,540 --> 00:16:33,360
Let's put a z-axis in.

405
00:16:33,580 --> 00:16:35,480
The z-axis comes out of the blackboard.

406
00:16:36,100 --> 00:16:38,180
So we're talking about rotations

407
00:16:38,180 --> 00:16:39,560
about the z-axis.

408
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:42,620
We could call this the z-component

409
00:16:42,620 --> 00:16:44,000
of the angular momentum.

410
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,900
It is the z-component of the angular momentum.

411
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:47,700
For the moment,

412
00:16:47,700 --> 00:16:48,800
I'm going to suppress that.

413
00:16:50,340 --> 00:16:51,120
All right,

414
00:16:51,120 --> 00:16:53,240
and M is the eigenvalue

415
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:54,640
of that angular momentum,

416
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:56,180
so strictly speaking,

417
00:16:56,380 --> 00:16:58,560
it's the eigenvalue of the z-component

418
00:16:58,560 --> 00:16:59,420
of angular momentum.

419
00:17:00,020 --> 00:17:02,200
Does it matter which axis is z

420
00:17:02,200 --> 00:17:03,800
and which axis is x?

421
00:17:03,880 --> 00:17:04,980
So you rotate the home?

422
00:17:04,980 --> 00:17:05,180
No,

423
00:17:05,180 --> 00:17:05,780
it doesn't matter,

424
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,319
but it's convention.

425
00:17:08,740 --> 00:17:09,280
Okay,

426
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:11,079
how do we find the eigenvectors?

427
00:17:11,500 --> 00:17:12,560
In other words,

428
00:17:12,579 --> 00:17:14,500
how do we find the wave functions

429
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:16,980
that correspond to eigenvectors?

430
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:18,119
And for that,

431
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:19,520
we just do the obvious thing.

432
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:24,000
We put in minus i h-bar d by d theta.

433
00:17:25,420 --> 00:17:28,760
That's L acting on psi of theta

434
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:32,320
is equal to M psi of theta.

435
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:35,860
That's a standard type of equation.

436
00:17:36,060 --> 00:17:38,660
The derivative of something

437
00:17:38,660 --> 00:17:41,400
is proportional to that something else.

438
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:42,870
We could bring the i

439
00:17:42,870 --> 00:17:44,240
h-bar over to the right-hand side,

440
00:17:44,840 --> 00:17:46,000
and that tells us

441
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:49,880
that the eigenvector with eigenvalue M

442
00:17:49,880 --> 00:17:50,520
is equal to m.

443
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:55,100
So that's the eigenvalue of M.

444
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:58,060
It is equal to e to the i M theta.

445
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:03,000
It's very similar to the case of ordinary momentum.

446
00:18:03,260 --> 00:18:03,540
Oops!

447
00:18:04,340 --> 00:18:05,740
What do I have missing here?

448
00:18:06,400 --> 00:18:08,020
I'm missing the h-bar.

449
00:18:08,220 --> 00:18:10,020
The h-bar would go downstairs here.

450
00:18:13,660 --> 00:18:16,180
Because if you divide by h-bar,

451
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,730
you see the thing that

452
00:18:17,730 --> 00:18:19,140
comes in is M over h-bar.

453
00:18:21,380 --> 00:18:21,900
Now,

454
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:24,900
unlike the case of ordinary linear momentum,

455
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:26,940
there's another constraint.

456
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:29,360
You know the other constraint.

457
00:18:29,520 --> 00:18:30,720
I'm sure that most of you know it,

458
00:18:30,760 --> 00:18:31,900
but let's spell it out anyway.

459
00:18:32,560 --> 00:18:34,860
The other constraint is that

460
00:18:34,860 --> 00:18:36,780
when theta is equal to 2 pi,

461
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:43,640
the wave function should be exactly what it was

462
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,260
when theta was equal to 0.

463
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:46,300
Why?

464
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,760
Because going around by 2 pi

465
00:18:48,760 --> 00:18:50,520
brings you back to the same point.

466
00:18:50,900 --> 00:18:53,360
And so if there's a sensible wave function,

467
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,080
that sensible wave function

468
00:18:55,100 --> 00:18:57,700
should be unchanged

469
00:18:58,380 --> 00:19:01,540
if you go around the circle by 2 pi.

470
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:04,970
So that says that e

471
00:19:04,970 --> 00:19:07,460
to the i M over h-bar

472
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:09,420
times 2 pi...

473
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:10,440
Well,

474
00:19:10,440 --> 00:19:10,740
let's see.

475
00:19:10,820 --> 00:19:11,380
First of all,

476
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:15,040
the wave function for theta equals 0

477
00:19:16,260 --> 00:19:17,300
is just 1.

478
00:19:18,020 --> 00:19:19,780
If I set theta equal to 0,

479
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:20,580
this is just 1.

480
00:19:20,940 --> 00:19:22,680
If I go around by 2 pi,

481
00:19:23,040 --> 00:19:24,660
the answer will be...

482
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:30,200
e to the i 2 pi M over h-bar.

483
00:19:30,780 --> 00:19:33,280
And that also has to be equal to 1.

484
00:19:36,100 --> 00:19:37,200
What's the constraint?

485
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,840
The constraint is that M over h-bar

486
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:40,920
has to be an integer.

487
00:19:42,780 --> 00:19:45,240
In order to make sure that the wave function

488
00:19:45,240 --> 00:19:46,420
comes back to itself,

489
00:19:46,560 --> 00:19:47,720
that it's single-valued,

490
00:19:47,740 --> 00:19:50,440
that it has a definite value at each point,

491
00:19:50,700 --> 00:19:52,000
it's necessary

492
00:19:53,500 --> 00:19:55,640
that the eigenvalues M

493
00:19:55,640 --> 00:19:59,680
be integer multiples of Planck's constant.

494
00:19:59,900 --> 00:20:01,080
So let's write that out.

495
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:07,780
M is equal to an integer...

496
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:10,500
No.

497
00:20:11,920 --> 00:20:12,720
Yeah.

498
00:20:13,860 --> 00:20:16,520
M is an integer times h-bar,

499
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:19,400
but the usual notation,

500
00:20:19,840 --> 00:20:20,840
the usual definition,

501
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:24,640
is to set M equal to the integer.

502
00:20:25,260 --> 00:20:27,260
Just call M the integer,

503
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:29,360
and then the angular momentum,

504
00:20:30,360 --> 00:20:32,760
the eigenvalue of the angular momentum,

505
00:20:33,860 --> 00:20:37,140
is an integer times h-bar.

506
00:20:39,140 --> 00:20:41,400
That's the quantization of angular momentum

507
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:42,800
in units of h-bar.

508
00:20:45,380 --> 00:20:45,960
Hereafter,

509
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,240
at least for the time being,

510
00:20:47,440 --> 00:20:48,940
I will drop h-bar,

511
00:20:49,860 --> 00:20:51,980
and we'll just say that the angular momentum

512
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,540
must be equal to an integer.

513
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:58,740
Angular momentum must be equal to an integer,

514
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:03,660
and that's a fundamental fact of quantum mechanics

515
00:21:09,400 --> 00:21:15,440
that we've known since the time of Niels Bohr.

516
00:21:18,820 --> 00:21:19,360
Okay,

517
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:21,980
now I have the following question for you.

518
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:24,840
Must it be the case...

519
00:21:24,840 --> 00:21:26,580
Let's suppose there's some energy.

520
00:21:27,380 --> 00:21:28,900
And let's suppose the energy

521
00:21:28,900 --> 00:21:30,420
depends on the angular momentum.

522
00:21:30,600 --> 00:21:31,280
Of course it does.

523
00:21:31,860 --> 00:21:32,640
The energy...

524
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,360
The bigger the angular momentum,

525
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:35,680
the bigger the energy.

526
00:21:35,960 --> 00:21:37,600
The particles whipping around

527
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:39,000
with a large angular momentum

528
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,500
that has more energy than a small angular momentum.

529
00:21:42,100 --> 00:21:44,500
So we expect that the angular momentum...

530
00:21:45,580 --> 00:21:48,380
that the energy will depend on the angular momentum.

531
00:21:50,380 --> 00:21:51,960
But must it be the case

532
00:21:51,960 --> 00:22:02,740
that the energy of a state with angular momentum m...

533
00:22:02,740 --> 00:22:04,640
That's the eigenvalue.

534
00:22:05,020 --> 00:22:06,640
Must it be the same

535
00:22:08,199 --> 00:22:10,549
as the energy of a

536
00:22:10,549 --> 00:22:12,900
state with angular momentum minus m?

537
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:16,620
What's the difference between m and minus m?

538
00:22:16,820 --> 00:22:17,040
Well,

539
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,480
the only difference is that

540
00:22:18,480 --> 00:22:21,940
positive angular momentum means the particle is moving.

541
00:22:21,940 --> 00:22:24,940
The particle is going around the circle counterclockwise.

542
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:29,650
And negative angular momentum

543
00:22:29,650 --> 00:22:31,260
means it's going around clockwise.

544
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:34,800
Take a vote.

545
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:38,160
How many people think that the energy must

546
00:22:38,160 --> 00:22:41,420
be the same for m and minus m?

547
00:22:42,960 --> 00:22:43,680
Of course.

548
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:44,660
I'll raise my hand too.

549
00:22:45,480 --> 00:22:46,610
How many think it does

550
00:22:46,610 --> 00:22:47,740
not have to be the same?

551
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:51,160
I will also raise my hand.

552
00:22:51,940 --> 00:22:52,480
I have a question.

553
00:22:52,900 --> 00:22:53,240
Yeah.

554
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:54,880
Just when you start out,

555
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:58,260
you said that theta goes beside theta minus epsilon.

556
00:22:58,880 --> 00:23:00,900
Should I think that then

557
00:23:00,900 --> 00:23:02,920
that implies we're looking at it

558
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,580
as going in a clockwise direction?

559
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:06,450
It's not telling you anything about

560
00:23:06,450 --> 00:23:07,900
the direction of motion of the particle.

561
00:23:08,060 --> 00:23:09,930
It's only telling you which

562
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:11,800
way you counted theta as positive.

563
00:23:12,840 --> 00:23:14,000
It's just telling...

564
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:16,700
It's like telling you I've decided

565
00:23:16,700 --> 00:23:19,400
that the positive x-axis points that way.

566
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:21,700
That tells me nothing about whether

567
00:23:21,940 --> 00:23:24,160
I'm walking that way or I'm walking this way.

568
00:23:26,060 --> 00:23:26,720
All right.

569
00:23:27,140 --> 00:23:30,220
It does set the definition of what

570
00:23:30,220 --> 00:23:33,300
you mean by positive and negative angular momentum.

571
00:23:34,340 --> 00:23:36,380
But it does not tell you whether

572
00:23:36,380 --> 00:23:38,420
the system has positive or negative angular momentum.

573
00:23:40,580 --> 00:23:41,100
Okay.

574
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:42,240
Art,

575
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,960
you raised your hand the second time.

576
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:45,840
Do you know an example where...

577
00:23:45,840 --> 00:23:48,480
I was just thinking that you

578
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:51,120
could have an asymmetrical field somewhere.

579
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:51,840
