883
00:36:56,850 --> 00:37:02,050
Let's look at the commutator of M with L.

884
00:37:02,210 --> 00:37:03,110
We know what L does.

885
00:37:03,850 --> 00:37:04,630
Here it is.

886
00:37:04,730 --> 00:37:06,610
It differentiates with respect to theta.

887
00:37:07,250 --> 00:37:08,370
What does M do?

888
00:37:08,570 --> 00:37:09,690
It reflects theta.

889
00:37:10,610 --> 00:37:13,290
So we can figure out what the commutator does.

890
00:37:13,570 --> 00:37:15,300
We can figure out what it does

891
00:37:15,300 --> 00:37:17,030
when it acts on a wave function.

892
00:37:17,190 --> 00:37:19,270
I'm going to act on a particular wave function.

893
00:37:19,870 --> 00:37:21,510
I'm going to act on the wave function

894
00:37:21,510 --> 00:37:25,350
e to the i m theta.

895
00:37:28,889 --> 00:37:31,670
A eigenvector of the angular momentum.

896
00:37:32,010 --> 00:37:33,450
I'm leaving h-bar out of it.

897
00:37:33,510 --> 00:37:34,110
We don't need it.

898
00:37:34,710 --> 00:37:37,030
And don't confuse big M with little m.

899
00:37:37,150 --> 00:37:38,440
Little m and big M have

900
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:39,730
nothing to do with each other.

901
00:37:39,950 --> 00:37:41,250
This stands for mirror.

902
00:37:41,490 --> 00:37:44,130
This stands for magnetic quantum number.

903
00:37:45,050 --> 00:37:45,530
Okay,

904
00:37:45,530 --> 00:37:46,830
let's see if we can work it out.

905
00:37:47,690 --> 00:37:49,590
Let's first do M L

906
00:37:50,230 --> 00:37:52,570
times e to the i m theta.

907
00:37:53,390 --> 00:37:55,280
What does L do when it

908
00:37:55,280 --> 00:37:57,170
hits e to the i m theta?

909
00:37:58,270 --> 00:37:59,690
It brings an M down.

910
00:38:00,010 --> 00:38:01,150
It brings an M down.

911
00:38:02,770 --> 00:38:03,290
Right.

912
00:38:03,590 --> 00:38:05,030
It just brings an M down.

913
00:38:05,550 --> 00:38:06,910
So this gives us

914
00:38:09,070 --> 00:38:10,810
M times little m

915
00:38:11,610 --> 00:38:13,230
e to the i m theta.

916
00:38:14,650 --> 00:38:16,670
And what does capital M do

917
00:38:18,410 --> 00:38:19,570
when it hits e to the i m theta?

918
00:38:19,570 --> 00:38:24,090
It just changes the sign of theta.

919
00:38:25,489 --> 00:38:26,090
Incidentally,

920
00:38:26,090 --> 00:38:28,190
once this is just a number,

921
00:38:28,869 --> 00:38:30,810
it doesn't matter which order

922
00:38:30,810 --> 00:38:32,490
big M and little m appear.

923
00:38:33,790 --> 00:38:35,490
And so this is just equal

924
00:38:35,490 --> 00:38:38,430
to little m times e

925
00:38:38,430 --> 00:38:41,370
to the minus i m theta.

926
00:38:43,150 --> 00:38:45,710
The big M just reflected theta.

927
00:38:47,090 --> 00:38:47,690
Okay,

928
00:38:47,690 --> 00:38:48,830
let's do it in the opposite order.

929
00:38:48,910 --> 00:38:49,550
L times e to the i m theta.

930
00:38:49,550 --> 00:38:49,990
So this is equal to M

931
00:38:51,050 --> 00:38:52,990
e to the i m theta.

932
00:38:54,330 --> 00:38:56,010
Now in the opposite order,

933
00:38:57,190 --> 00:38:58,570
first M acts.

934
00:38:59,510 --> 00:39:01,090
And that gives us L.

935
00:39:01,990 --> 00:39:03,210
When M acts,

936
00:39:03,210 --> 00:39:04,770
it changes the sign of theta

937
00:39:04,770 --> 00:39:07,690
and gives us e to the minus i m theta.

938
00:39:09,130 --> 00:39:10,950
But what happens when L hits

939
00:39:10,950 --> 00:39:12,650
e to the minus i m theta?

940
00:39:13,990 --> 00:39:15,250
Anybody got a good idea?

941
00:39:19,550 --> 00:39:21,510
It brings down a minus M.

942
00:39:25,290 --> 00:39:26,650
By reflecting,

943
00:39:27,250 --> 00:39:29,430
we've changed the sign of the angular momentum.

944
00:39:29,790 --> 00:39:31,650
So the angular momentum operator

945
00:39:31,650 --> 00:39:33,790
gives us the minus of what it gave before.

946
00:39:34,130 --> 00:39:35,830
It gives us minus M

947
00:39:36,550 --> 00:39:38,310
e to the minus i m theta.

948
00:39:39,850 --> 00:39:43,410
So the answer is that M and L,

949
00:39:43,630 --> 00:39:46,270
angular momentum and the reflection operator,

950
00:39:46,430 --> 00:39:47,970
